result.execSummary:
The defendant Richard L Keller was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Child Pornography [Modifiers: Penalty - Possession of Child Pornography], a class D felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.12(1m).
  • Possession of Child Pornography [Modifiers: Penalty - Possession of Child Pornography], a class D felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.12(1m).
  • Possession of Child Pornography [Modifiers: Penalty - Possession of Child Pornography], a class D felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.12(1m).
  • Possession of Child Pornography [Modifiers: Penalty - Possession of Child Pornography], a class D felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.12(1m).
  • Possession of Child Pornography [Modifiers: Penalty - Possession of Child Pornography], a class D felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.12(1m).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Consecutive to: any sentences defendant is currently serving.

superMiscConds.notes: lf extended supervision is revoked and the defendant will have a mandatory release from prison, a civil judgment shall be entered for the balance due.

Defendant shall not have direct or indirect contact with anyone under age 18 without prior agent approval. 
Defendant shall not possess or use any device with internet access without prior agent approval and only to be used for employment purposes. 
Defendant shall not possess any pornographic materials.

Defendant shall participate in sex offender assessment, counseling and treatment and all other counseling or treatment programs directed by the probation agent. 
Defendant to complete the sex offender treatment program. 
Defendant shall comply with sex offender registration. 
Defendant shall provide a biological specimen for DNA analysis.  Defendant has the right to request expungement of DNA analysis in writing through the Department of Justice.
Defendant shall pay Dept of Corrections supervision fees. 
Defendant shall maintain absolute sobriety.

supervisions.notes: Consecutive to: any sentences defendant is currently serving.
